# Add Server-Driven WebSocket Commands to BiofeedbackClient

The current [BiofeedbackClient.cs](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/BiofeedbackClient.cs) uses a local random-trigger system in [Update()](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/MoveBirds.cs#13-20) during therapy mode to fire events (fireflies, birds). The goal is to add **three new WebSocket command handlers** so the Python server can directly control:

1. **Breathing ball repositioning** — smooth move to a random point on a circle around the XR camera
2. **Fireflies visibility** — show/hide the left and right firefly groups
3. **Bird flyovers** — trigger bird flyover sequences

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These new commands run **alongside** the existing local random timer logic in [Update()](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/MoveBirds.cs#13-20). Should the local timer logic be **removed** or kept as a fallback?  
> Currently I'm keeping it untouched — please confirm.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The current script has no reference to the XR camera. I'll add an `XROrigin` reference and locate the camera via `Camera.main` (or `XROrigin.Camera`). Please confirm which approach you prefer, or if the camera reference is already available elsewhere.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The **circle radius** and **movement speed** for the breathing ball repositioning need sensible defaults. I'll use `radius = 2.0f` and `moveDuration = 2.0f` seconds (smooth Lerp). Adjust as needed.

## Proposed Changes

### BiofeedbackClient

#### [MODIFY] [BiofeedbackClient.cs](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/BiofeedbackClient.cs)

**1. New fields** (added after existing field block):

```csharp
[Header("Breathing Ball Movement")]
public float ballCircleRadius = 2.0f;   // radius of circle around player
public float ballMoveDuration = 2.0f;   // seconds for smooth transition

private bool _ballMoving = false;
private Vector3 _ballMoveStart;
private Vector3 _ballMoveTarget;
private float _ballMoveElapsed;
```

**2. New [ProcessMessage](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/BiofeedbackClient.cs#270-307) cases** inside the `switch (msg.action)` block:

| WebSocket action string | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `"move_breathing_ball"` | Pick a random angle, compute a point on a circle of `ballCircleRadius` around `Camera.main`, start smooth coroutine/lerp move of `breathingBall` |
| `"show_fireflies"` | `firefliesLeft.SetActive(true); firefliesRight.SetActive(true);` |
| `"hide_fireflies"` | `firefliesLeft.SetActive(false); firefliesRight.SetActive(false);` |
| `"start_birds_flyover"` | Reset bird positions to start, activate both bird GameObjects, set movement flag for [Update()](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/MoveBirds.cs#13-20) translation |

**3. Smooth ball movement** — handled in [Update()](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/MoveBirds.cs#13-20) via a simple Lerp block:

```csharp
if (_ballMoving)
{
    _ballMoveElapsed += Time.deltaTime;
    float t = Mathf.Clamp01(_ballMoveElapsed / ballMoveDuration);
    t = t * t * (3f - 2f * t); // smoothstep
    breathingBall.transform.position = Vector3.Lerp(_ballMoveStart, _ballMoveTarget, t);
    if (t >= 1f) _ballMoving = false;
}
```

**4. Helper method** `MoveBreathingBallToRandomPoint()`:

```csharp
private void MoveBreathingBallToRandomPoint()
{
    Transform cam = Camera.main.transform;
    float angle = UnityEngine.Random.Range(0f, 360f) * Mathf.Deg2Rad;
    Vector3 offset = new Vector3(Mathf.Cos(angle), 0f, Mathf.Sin(angle)) * ballCircleRadius;
    _ballMoveTarget = cam.position + offset;
    _ballMoveTarget.y = breathingBall.transform.position.y; // keep same height
    _ballMoveStart = breathingBall.transform.position;
    _ballMoveElapsed = 0f;
    _ballMoving = true;
}
```

**5. Helper method** `StartBirdsFlyover()`:

```csharp
private void StartBirdsFlyover()
{
    birdsSmall.transform.position = birdsSmallStart;
    birdsLarge.transform.position = birdsLargeStart;
    birdsSmall.SetActive(true);
    birdsLarge.SetActive(true);
    birdsSmallRun = true;
    birdsLargeRun = true;
}
```

**6. Bird movement in [Update()](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/MoveBirds.cs#13-20)** — add after ball movement block:

```csharp
if (birdsSmallRun)
    birdsSmall.transform.Translate(Vector3.forward * 2f * Time.deltaTime);
if (birdsLargeRun)
    birdsLarge.transform.Translate(Vector3.forward * 2f * Time.deltaTime);
```

**7. Updated [ServerMessage](file:///c:/Users/mkikolski/Biofeedback%20NCNI/Assets/Scripts/BiofeedbackClient.cs#257-267) class** — add optional field:

```csharp
public float angle; // optional: specific angle for breathing ball (degrees)
```

If the server sends an `angle` field, the ball will move to that specific point on the circle instead of a random one.

